Limitations. Both benchmarks are classic control tasks; generalisation to continuous-action or high-dimensional environments remains open. Co-evolution never outperforms no-plasticity evolution, and is marginally counterproductive under non-stationarity—a stronger test would use a benchmark where the GA cannot find robust topologies within 200 generations, forcing reliance on within-lifetime adaptation. The random-RNN sample is small (65 competent networks), and the weight distribution differs from MorphoNAS (uniform vs distance-dependent), introducing a potential confound. The plasticity rule (Eq. ) is deliberately simple; richer mechanisms (
            , 
          ) may interact differently with developmental topologies.
